<p><b>Zoroaster</b> (<a href="/wiki/Latin" title="Latin">Latinized</a> from <a href="#Greek_Zoroaster" title="">Greek variants</a>) or <b>Zarathushtra</b> (from <a href="/wiki/Avestan" title="Avestan" class="mw-redirect">Avestan</a> <i>Zaraθuštra</i>), also referred to as <b>Zartosht</b> (<a href="/wiki/Persian_language" title="Persian language">Persian</a>: <span lang="fa" xml:lang="fa">زرتشت</span>), was an <a href="/wiki/Ancient_Iranian_peoples" title="Ancient Iranian peoples">ancient Iranian</a> prophet and religious poet. The hymns attributed to him, the <a href="/wiki/Gathas" title="Gathas">Gathas</a>, are at the liturgical core of <a href="/wiki/Zoroastrianism" title="Zoroastrianism">Zoroastrianism</a>.</p>
